This paper deals with domain adaptation, which is a common problem in machine learning and computer vision. The paper proposes a new method for addressing the issue of class weight bias in domain adaptation, which is a problem that arises frequently in real-world scenarios. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
